Usage: cunf [OPTION]... NET [SPECIFICATION]

where NET is a path to an .ll_net input file.  Allowed OPTIONS are:
 --cutoff {erv,mcm,N}  Sets the algorithm used for computing cutoff events:
                        - erv: Esparza-Romer-Vogler
                        - mcm: McMillan's algorithm
                        - N : where N is a non-negative number; every event of
                              depth N is declared cutoff; with N=0 the cutoff
                              algorthm is effectively disabled
 --save FILE           Saves a copy of the unfolding to FILE
 --help                Shows this message
 --version             Prints version information

For more information, see https://code.google.com/p/cunf/

